case_circumstances:
Complete atraumatic human skull without mandible found by two hunters on shoreline.   
--"It is excellently preserved and is filled with grass-blades, probably introduced by nesting animal and contains some sand although far less that it would if it had been buried in sandm.  The fact that is was found by hunters, isolated, separated from the rest of the body, suggests decomposition elsewhere, perhaps in Delaware Bay (depending on currents) and deposited on the shore by waves and wind.  The lack of mineral staining on this skull, usual in skulls under water in a quiet spot, fits this guess. (excerpt from letter to Delaware State Police from Ali Z. Hameli, M.D., Delaware State Medical Examiner  dated 122965.
